sublevels.theory:
Java provides classes in `java.io` to read/write files.

**Writing a file:**
```java
import java.io.*;
FileWriter fw = new FileWriter("output.txt");
fw.write("Hello, World!");
fw.close();
```

**Reading a file line by line:**
```java
BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("input.txt"));
String line;
while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
br.close();
```

**try-with-resources:** automatically closes the stream:
```java
try (BufferedReader b = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("f.txt"))) {
    System.out.println(b.readLine());
}
```

**`java.nio.file` (Java 7+):** modern file API:
```java
import java.nio.file.*;
Path path = Path.of("data.txt");

// Write all text at once
Files.writeString(path, "Hello\n", StandardOpenOption.APPEND);

// Read all lines
List<String> lines = Files.readAllLines(path);

// Stream of lines
Files.lines(path).filter(l -> l.startsWith("#")).forEach(System.out::println);

// Directory listing
Files.list(Path.of(".")).forEach(System.out::println);
```

**`Files.copy`, `Files.move`, `Files.delete`** — common operations.

**`ObjectOutputStream` / `ObjectInputStream`** — Java object serialization.
